post_text: Happy Sunday my friends! I wanted to share with everyone what’s happening in guidance classes with our Eagles and Rebels! I spent my week with kiddos working on change and tools we have at our disposal to help ourselves when we might be struggling. My little people learned about their heart thoughts and my older friends learned about breathing and we practiced with wave breathing. What they learned is that they ALWAYS have these things with them and no one can ever take them away! If you ever have any questions or need anything at all, please reach out! Sending all the love out today! 🙏🏾💗 Mrs. Myers 💗

post_text: This is a great read about self-care!
shared_text:
The Gottman Institute
June 11 at 5:00 PM ·

Children, just like adults, benefit greatly from consistent and deliberate self-care activities.

We all need to learn how to take care of ourselves, and performing self-care activities with your children is an excellent way to model healthy lifestyle choices for your children. By making self-care a daily practice, parents provide opportunities to build rituals of connection and create a system of shared meaning.

Support your kids’ long-term well-being by making healthy and meaningful choices that encourage growth, connection, expression, and stability. Give these self-care activities a try or sit down with your child and invite them to brainstorm new ideas unique to their interests.

Learn more about the value of consistent and deliberate self-care activities: https://bit.ly/3fcEUte

post_text: Open to students in the Lawton-Bronson District.
shared_text:
Lawton-Bronson Community School District
March 23 at 4:38 PM ·

The Lawton-Bronson Nutrition Department received a No Kid Hungry Grant and will provide opportunities for families to drive through or walk up to pick up meals. We will be implementing the emergency food program starting Wednesday, March 25, 2020. CHILDREN MUST BE PRESENT IN ORDER FOR MEALS TO BE PROVIDED. Meals for children ages 1-18 will be available at the Bronson Elementary (backside of school) and the Lawton High School (backside of school) from 11:00 a.m. to 12:00 pm Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. Parents do not need to be present with their children if students are able to pick up the food items themselves. This free meal is being provided for all children 18 and under living in the Lawton-Bronson CSD.
Check your email or the attached picture for more information.
